items.title: The FTC’s data-sharing order against GM is finally settled
items.summary: The order, first proposed a year ago, bans GM from collecting and then selling geolocation data to third parties, like data brokers and insurance companies.
items.author: Kirsten Korosec

items.title: India’s Emversity doubles valuation as it scales workers AI can’t replace
items.summary: Emversity has raised $30 million in a new round as it scales job-ready training in India.
items.author: Jagmeet Singh

items.title: Musk denies awareness of Grok sexual underage images as California AG launches probe
items.summary: The California attorney general has opened a formal investigation into Elon Musk's xAI after its chatbot Grok began generating nonconsensual sexual images of real women and even children.
items.author: Rebecca Bellan

items.title: OpenAI signs deal, worth $10B, for compute from Cerebras
items.summary: The collaboration will help OpenAI's models deliver faster response times for more difficult or time-consuming tasks, the companies said.
items.author: Lucas Ropek

items.title: Netflix’s first original video podcasts feature Pete Davidson and Michael Irvin
items.summary: As Netflix tries to take down YouTube’s dominance in the podcast space, it's getting new originals with Pete Davidson and Michael Irvin.
items.author: Lauren Forristal

items.title: App downloads declined again in 2025, but consumer spending soared to nearly $156B
items.summary: Global app downloads were down, but consumer spending was up to nearly $156B in 2025.
items.author: Sarah Perez

items.title: AI models are starting to crack high-level math problems
items.summary: Since the release of GPT 5.2, AI tools have become inescapable in high-level mathematics.
items.author: Russell Brandom

items.title: Blackstone, General Atlantic-backed Liftoff Mobile files for IPO
items.summary: The company offers a platform that helps mobile app developers market their wares and has an army of bankers working on its IPO.
items.author: Julie Bort

items.title: Digg launches its new Reddit rival to the public
items.summary: Digg, a reboot of an earlier social news site, is now relaunching as a Reddit competitor focused on communities.
items.author: Sarah Perez

items.title: Google’s Trends Explore page gets new Gemini capabilities
items.summary: The Trends Explore page for users to analyze search interest just got a major upgrade. It now uses Gemini to identify and compare relevant trends.

items.title: Bandcamp takes a stand against AI music, banning it from the platform
items.summary: "We want musicians to keep making music, and for fans to have confidence that the music they find on Bandcamp was created by humans," the company said.
items.author: Amanda Silberling

items.title: Bill Gates-backed Type One Energy raises $87M ahead of $250M Series B
items.summary: Type One Energy has raised more than $160 million from investors to date. The new funding will help the company further refine its stellarator technology.
items.author: Tim De Chant

items.title: Robotics software maker Skild AI hits $14B valuation
items.summary: Skild AI, which is building general-purpose robotic software, just raised a $1.4 billion funding round led by SoftBank.

items.title: Gemini’s new beta feature provides proactive responses based on your photos, emails, and more
items.summary: Personal Intelligence is off by default, as users have the option to choose if and when they want to connect their Google apps to Gemini.
items.author: Aisha Malik

items.title: AI security firm, depthfirst, announces $40 million Series A
items.summary: The company used an AI-native platform to help companies fight threats.

items.title: US cargo tech company publicly exposed its shipping systems and customer data to the web
items.summary: Shipping tech company Bluspark left internal plaintext passwords, including those of executives, exposed to the internet, at a time when hacks in the shipping industry are on the rise.

items.title: YouTube now has a way for parents to block kids from watching Shorts
items.summary: Parents will be able to toggle the Shorts time limit on connected children's accounts.
items.author: Amanda Silberling

items.title: Tesla will only offer subscriptions for Full Self-Driving (Supervised) going forward
items.summary: It's a huge change to Tesla's approach with FSD, and it could impact Musk's $1T pay package and the company's myriad legal troubles.

items.title: VoiceRun nabs $5.5M to build a voice agent factory
items.summary: VoiceRun, a startup that creates voice agents, raised $5.5 million in a round led by Flybridge.

items.title: Meta to reportedly lay off 10% of Reality Labs staff
items.summary: The publication noted that Reality Labs had roughly 15,000 employees, and the job cuts could impact over 1,000 people.
